x4freetext: Data are superseded
Cross sections for discrete gamma-ray production in
interaction of 14.6 MeV neutrons with light and medium
heavy nuclei
Neutron generator of the Institute of Physics
of the Slovak Academy of Sciences, Bratislava.
Coincidence was required of the
gamma rays with the associated alpha`s.
The 244 cm**3 HPGe gamma detector was
placed at an angle of 125 degree with respect to the
neutron beam. The detector was housed in a tungsten
shield to decrease the background.
Production cross
section of the 1434 keV transition.
Corrections have been made for attenuation of gamma
and neutron fluxes and for in-sample scattering.
Component of uncertainties are given as:
- Net peak area, 3-20%
- Reference cross section, 4-5%
- Detector efficiency, 3%
- Neutron multiple scattering, less than 3%
- Correction for gamma absorption, 1.5%
Data are from tables 4, 7 and  9 of
Numerical values in subentries 2-8
were updated, monitor data added, sources of
uncertainty added
